## Examples and Use Cases

- Language revival efforts restoring relational meaning to ceremonial terms  
- A suppressed idea (e.g., from indigenous medicine) being reactivated structurally—not symbolically—in modern science  
- Reintegration of lived experience into cognitive graphs following trauma or epistemic distortion
